----------------------------------------------------------------
PRACTICAL 4(a): Automate Any Process Using Basic Recording
----------------------------------------------------------------

AIM:
To use UiPath Basic Recording to automate opening Notepad,
typing text, and saving the file.

THEORY:
Basic Recording in UiPath captures individual clicks and keystrokes
on any application (desktop or web). Unlike Web or Desktop
recordings, Basic recording does NOT use containers (Attach Window/
Browser). Each action is recorded individually. It is useful for
simple one-off automations across multiple applications.

PRE-REQUISITES:
- Notepad (built into Windows)
- UiPath Studio installed

STEPS:

Step 1: Create a New Project
  - Open UiPath Studio.
  - Click "New Project" > "Process".
  - Name it: basic_recording_demo
  - Click "Create".

Step 2: Open Notepad Manually
  - Press Windows key + R, type "notepad", press Enter.
  - Notepad should be open and visible on screen.

Step 3: Start Basic Recording
  - In UiPath Studio, go to the "Design" tab in the top ribbon.
  - Click "Recording" > "Basic".
  - The Basic Recording toolbar appears at the top of the screen.

Step 4: Record Clicking Inside Notepad
  - Click "Click" in the Recording toolbar.
  - Click inside the white area of Notepad (the text editing area).
  - UiPath will highlight the element in blue and record the click.

Step 5: Record Typing Text
  - Click "Type" in the Recording toolbar.
  - Click inside Notepad's text area.
  - A dialog box appears asking what to type.
  - Type: "Hello! This is a Basic Recording demo in UiPath."
  - Click OK.

Step 6: Record Saving the File (Ctrl+S)
  - Click "Type" in the Recording toolbar.
  - Click inside Notepad.
  - In the dialog, leave text blank and set special keys.
  - Click the "Special Keys" checkbox or manually type: [k(ctrl+s)]
  - (Alternatively, use "Send Hotkey" from the toolbar if available.)

Step 7: Handle Save Dialog (if file is unsaved)
  - If Notepad shows a "Save As" dialog:
    * Click "Click" in Recording toolbar.
    * Click the "Save" button.

Step 8: Stop Recording
  - Press Escape or click "Save & Exit".
  - UiPath generates the sequence of activities.

Step 9: Run
  - Close Notepad if open (to test fresh).
  - Re-open Notepad manually.
  - Press F5 in UiPath Studio.
  - The bot will click in Notepad and type the text automatically.

EXPECTED OUTPUT:
  Notepad will contain the text:
  "Hello! This is a Basic Recording demo in UiPath."

